                            <comment id="16364682" author="kiszk" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2018 19:55:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am working for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16364686" author="dongjoon" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2018 20:00:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you so much, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kiszk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kiszk&quot;&gt;kiszk&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16365931" author="kiszk" created="Thu, 15 Feb 2018 17:02:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I realized that an issue in this test case. I think that this test case expects to try memory allocation in&#160;&lt;tt&gt;grow()&lt;/tt&gt; method four times. However, since the allocated memory is reused, this test performed memory allocation only once with &lt;tt&gt;roundToWord(ARRAY_MAX / 2)&lt;/tt&gt;. No memory allocations occur with other sizes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I updated this test to perform four memory allocations with &lt;tt&gt;4g&lt;/tt&gt; heap size,  an exception occurs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
